{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Num|23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","chapter":23,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":1,"text":"Then Balaam said to Balak, “Build me seven altars here and prepare seven bulls and seven rams for me.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":2,"text":"So Balak did as Balaam directed, and they offered a bull and a ram on each altar.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":3,"text":"Balaam said to Balak, “Stay here by your burnt offering while I am gone. Maybe the Lord will meet with me. I will tell you whatever he reveals to me.” So he went to a barren hill.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":4,"text":"God met with him and Balaam said to him, “I have arranged seven altars and offered a bull and a ram on each altar.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":5,"text":"Then the Lord put a message in Balaam’s mouth and said, “Return to Balak and say what I tell you.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":6,"text":"So he returned to Balak, who was standing there by his burnt offering with all the officials of Moab.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":7,"text":"Balaam proclaimed his poem:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":8,"text":"How can I curse someone God has not cursed?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":9,"text":"I see them from the top of rocky cliffs,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":10,"text":"Who has counted the dust of Jacob","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":11,"text":"“What have you done to me?” Balak asked Balaam. “I brought you to curse my enemies, but look, you have only blessed them!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":12,"text":"He answered, “Shouldn’t I say exactly what the Lord puts in my mouth?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":13,"text":"Then Balak said to him, “Please come with me to another place where you can see them. You will only see the outskirts of their camp; you won’t see all of them. From there, put a curse on them for me.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":14,"text":"So Balak took him to Lookout Field on top of Pisgah, built seven altars, and offered a bull and a ram on each altar.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":15,"text":"Balaam said to Balak, “Stay here by your burnt offering while I seek the Lord over there.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":16,"text":"The Lord met with Balaam and put a message in his mouth. Then he said, “Return to Balak and say what I tell you.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":17,"text":"So he returned to Balak, who was standing there by his burnt offering with the officials of Moab. Balak asked him, “What did the Lord say?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":18,"text":"Balaam proclaimed his poem:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":19,"text":"God is not a man, that he might lie,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":20,"text":"I have indeed received a command to bless;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":21,"text":"He considers no disaster for Jacob;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":22,"text":"God brought them out of Egypt;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":23,"text":"There is no magic curse against Jacob","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":24,"text":"A people rise up like a lioness;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":25,"text":"Then Balak told Balaam, “Don’t curse them and don’t bless them!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":26,"text":"But Balaam answered him, “Didn’t I tell you: Whatever the Lord says, I must do?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":27,"text":"Again Balak said to Balaam, “Please come. I will take you to another place. Maybe it will be agreeable to God that you can put a curse on them for me there.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":28,"text":"So Balak took Balaam to the top of Peor, which overlooks the wasteland.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":29,"text":"Balaam told Balak, “Build me seven altars here and prepare seven bulls and seven rams for me.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","bookOrder":3,"chapter":23,"verse":30,"text":"So Balak did as Balaam said and offered a bull and a ram on each altar.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Num","chapter":23,"paragraphStarts":[1,4,