 by your burnt offering while I seek the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" over there.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" met with Balaam and put a message in his mouth. Then he said, “Return to Balak and say what I tell you.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So he returned to Balak, who was standing there by his burnt offering with the officials of Moab. Balak asked him, “What did the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":" say?”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Balaam proclaimed his poem:"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"God is not a man, that he might lie,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I have indeed received a command to bless;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He considers no disaster for Jacob;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"God brought them out of Egypt;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"There is no magic curse against Jacob"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"A people rise up like a lioness;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then Balak told Balaam, “Don’t curse them and don’t bless them!”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Num:23:26","p